  <static seed="1230" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/FractionArithmetic/SubtractFractions05.pg">
    <statement><p>Subtract: <m>\displaystyle{\frac{17}{12} - \frac{7}{12}}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="11" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>{\frac{5}{6}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To subtract two fractions with the same denominator, we simply subtract the numerators and keep the denominator unchanged.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   \frac{17}{12} - \frac{7}{12}
        \amp = \frac{17 - 7}{12} \\
        \amp = \frac{10}{12} \amp \hbox{We can reduce this by dividing 2 into both the numerator and the denominator.
}\\
        \amp = \frac{5}{6} \\
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
</solution>
